adjectives.description: sheltered (comparative more sheltered, superlative most sheltered)

entries.meaning: Protected, as from wind or weather.
examples: The boat was much safer, during the storm, in the sheltered cove.

entries.meaning: (sociology) (Of a person) who grew up being overprotected by parents or other guardians; often implies a lack of social skills or worldly experience
simple past tense and past participle of shelter
